  "response": "The first touch screen phone was invented by IBM. The phone, known as the IBM Simon Personal Communicator, was developed by IBM engineer Frank Canova and his team. It was introduced in 1992 and released to the public on August 16, 1994. The IBM Simon was manufactured by Mitsubishi Electric and was sold through BellSouth in the United States.",
